'''Ali Ahmad Ali Azaizeh''' ({{langx|ar|علي العزايزة}}; born 13 April 2004) is a Jordanian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|winger]] for [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al Shabab Club|Al-Shabab]], on loan from [[Kuwait Premier League]] club [[Kazma SC|Kazma]]. Born in Germany, he plays for the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hassan |first1=Fayez |title=علي العزايزة نجم أردني متوهج يمضي على خطى موسى التعمري |url=https://www.winwin.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B2%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B2%D8%A9-%D9%86%D8%AC%D9%85-%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86%D9%8A-%D9%85%D8%AA%D9%88%D9%87%D8%AC-%D9%8A%D9%85%D8%B6%D9%8A-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%AE%D8%B7%D9%89-%D9%85%D9%88%D8%B3%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%B9%D9%85%D8%B1%D9%8A |website=winwin.com |publisher=WinWin |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=12 January 2026}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in Germany, Azaizeh fell in love with football while living there at a young age.<ref name="kooora1"/> His parents moved to Germany in the early 1990s to pursue their international studies. When he returned to Jordan, he quickly joined [[Prince Ali bin Hussein|Prince Ali]]'s youth centers, revealing his talent in the process.<ref name="kooora1"/> He represented [[Al-Ramtha SC|Al-Ramtha]]'s under-14 category, and rose through the club's ranks.

===Al-Ramtha===
Azaizeh was an unused substitute at the age of sixteen as Al-Ramtha finished as runners-up in the [[2020 Jordan Shield Cup]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=JFA - اصدار جدول مباريات بطولة درع الاتحاد لموسم 2020|url=https://www.jfa.com.jo/news.php?id=27391&title=اصدار-جدول-مباريات-بطولة-درع-الاتحاد-لموسم-2020|access-date=2023-05-23|website=JFA - الاتحاد الاردني لكرة القدم|language=ar}}</ref> and he made his senior debut during the [[2020 Jordanian Pro League]] season during the 1–0 victory against [[Sahab SC|Sahab]] on 9 August 2020, and he also played against [[Al-Faisaly SC|Al-Faisaly]] on 31 October 2020. He was a part of the club's league-winning season in [[2021 Jordanian Pro League|2021]].<ref name="kooora1"/> He then won the [[Jordan Super Cup]] in 2022.

==== Al-Khaldiya (loan) ====
On 16 January 2025, Azaizeh signed with [[Bahraini Premier League]] club [[Al-Khaldiya SC|Al-Khaldiya]] on loan.<ref>{{cite web |title=رسميا.. العزايزة ينتقل للخالدية البحريني |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1382017&o=n8000071 |website=kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |access-date=19 January 2025 |language=Arabic |date=16 January 2025}}</ref> On 29 January, Al-Khaldiya were crowned the first-ever champions of the [[2024–25 Khalid Bin Hamad Cup|Khalid Bin Hamad Cup]], with Azaizeh scoring the winning goal and receiving the best player of the match.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Salomon |first1=Patrick Oliver |title=gdnonline.com |url=https://www.gdnonline.com/Details/1343251|website=gdnonline.com |publisher=GDN Online |access-date=3 July 2025 |language=English |date=29 January 2025}}</ref> He did not however score a single league goal for the club.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Ali Al-Azaizeh |url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/player/99047/Ali_Al_Azaizeh.html |website=National Football Teams}}</ref>

===Kazma===
On 30 May 2025, [[Al-Ramtha SC|Al-Ramtha]] agreed to sell Azaizeh to [[Kuwait Premier League]] club [[Kazma SC|Kazma]] for 220 thousand dollars, with Azaizeh signing on a three-year contract. A member of Al-Ramtha's board of directors revealed that the club will receive up to 170 thousand dollars from Kazma and 50 thousand dollars from the player.<ref>{{cite web |title=الرمثا يصدر موهبة جديدة.. ويبحث عن محلّيين وأجانب |url=https://jfranews.com.jo/article/499121 |website=jfranews.com |publisher=Jfra News |access-date=3 July 2025 |language=Arabic |date=31 May 2025}}</ref> The signing was confirmed by Kazma on 7 June 2025.<ref>{{cite web |date=7 June 2025 |title=اكتملت العيدية . . 🟠💥👌 |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/DKmyCuEKA-j/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&igsh=MzRlODBiNWFlZA== |access-date=3 July 2025 |website=instagram.com |publisher=Kazma SC |language=Arabic}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=العربي وكاظمة يوقفان بعضهما بالتعادل السلبي |url=https://www.alanba.com.kw/1325892 |website=alanba.com.kw |publisher=Al-Anba |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=28 September 2025}}</ref>

Azaizeh was rumoured to leave Kazma to join an Emirati club with a significant fee, as well as to make the switch to join the [[United Arab Emirates national football team|Emirati national team]], to which he declined the rumours of naturalizing via an [[Instagram]] story, and rejecting the offer as a result.<ref>{{cite web |title=العزايزة يرفض تمثيل المنتخب الإماراتي |url=https://factjo.com/news/130305?slug=alaazayz-yrfd-tmthyl-almntkhb-alamaraty-1769344830 |website=factjo.com |publisher=FactJO |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=25 January 2026}}</ref> Days later, he became linked to move to Saudi club [[Al Shabab Club|Al Shabab]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hassan |first1=Fayez |title=الأردني علي العزايزة يقترب من الاحتراف في الشباب السعودي |url=https://www.winwin.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86%D9%8A-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B2%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B2%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D9%82%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%A8-%D9%85%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%AD%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%81-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B4%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%8A?amp |website=winwin.com |publisher=WinWin |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=27 January 2026}}</ref>

====Al-Shabab (loan)====
On 27 January 2026, Azaizeh signed with [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al Shabab Club|Al-Shabab]] on a six-month loan.<ref>{{cite web |title=الأردني علي العزايزة إلى الشباب|url=https://aawsat.com/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9-%D8%B3%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%A9/5234476-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86%D9%8A-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B2%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B2%D8%A9-%D8%A5%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B4%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A8}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=العزايزة: النمر جاهز للتحدي وإسعاد مدرجات الشباب.. فيديو |url=https://slaati.com/2026/01/29/p2768893.html |website=slaati.com |publisher=Slaati |access-date=30 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=29 January 2026}}</ref> Two days later, he made his debut for the club as a substitute in a 4–0 win against [[Al-Hazem FC|Al-Hazem]].<ref>{{cite web |title=علي العزايزة يظهر اليوم بدوري روشن السعودي |url=https://www.factjo.com/news/130629 |website=factjo.com |publisher=FactJO |access-date=30 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=29 January 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Hassan |first1=Fayez |title=في أول ظهور.. علي العزايزة يكسب قلوب جماهير الشباب السعودي |url=https://www.winwin.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84-%D8%B8%D9%87%D9%88%D8%B1-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B2%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B2%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D9%83%D8%B3%D8%A8-%D9%82%D9%84%D9%88%D8%A8-%D8%AC%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%87%D9%8A%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B4%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%8A |website=winwin.com |publisher=WinWIn |access-date=30 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=30 January 2026}}</ref>

He scored his first goal for Al-Shabab on 17 February 2026 during the 13–0 victory against [[Al-Tadamun Hadramaut]] in the [[2025–26 AGCFF Gulf Club Champions League|AGCFF Gulf Club Champions League]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=17 February 2026 |title=Al-Shabab 13–0 Al-Tadamun Hadramaut |url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/en/soccer/match/2026-02-17/al-shabab-saudi-club-vs-al-tadamun-hadramaut-scsc/3920509 |access-date=20 February 2026 |website=Global Sports Archive}}</ref> On 14 April, he scored his first two [[2025–26 Saudi Pro League|league]] goals for the club in a 2–2 draw against [[Al Qadsiah FC|Al-Qadsiah]].

==International career==
===Youth===
Azaizeh is a youth international for Jordan, having represented the Jordanian [[Jordan national under-23 football team|under-23]] team at the [[2024 AFC U-23 Asian Cup]] that took place in Qatar.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.jfa.jo/news.php?id=29736&title=%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%B7%D9%86%D9%8A-%D8%AA23-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%AA%D9%87-%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%B7%D9%88%D9%84%D8%A9-%D8%BA%D8%B1%D8%A8-%D8%A2%D8%B3%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%A9|title=إعلان القائمة الأولية للمنتخب الوطني ت23 لمعسكر قطر والنهائيات الآسيوية|trans-title=Announcing the preliminary list of the U23 national team for the Qatar camp and the Asian Cup finals|publisher=Jordan Football Association|date=6 April 2024}}</ref>

Azaizeh came back to the under-23 program for the [[2026 AFC U-23 Asian Cup qualification|2026 AFC U-23 Asian Cup qualifiers]], to which he registered a goal agsinst [[Chinese Taipei national under-23 football team|Chinese Taipei]] and [[Turkmenistan national under-23 football team|Turkmenistan]], respectively.<ref>{{cite web |title=المنتخب الوطني ت23 يحقق فوزا كبيرا على تايبيه الصينية بالتصفيات الآسيوية |url=https://www.ammonnews.net/article/946357 |website=ammonnews.net |publisher=Ammon News |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=6 September 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title="الأولمبي" ينجز مهمة تركمانستان ويبلغ نهائيات آسيا للمرة السابعة |url=https://alghad.com/Section-180/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D9%86%D8%AC%D8%B2-%D9%85%D9%87%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%AA%D8%B1%D9%83%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%A8%D9%84%D8%BA-%D9%86%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A2%D8%B3%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D9%84%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%B9%D8%A9-2045254 |website=alghad.com |publisher=Al-Ghad |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=9 September 2025}}</ref> Azaizeh was initially not called up to the under-23 roster for the [[2026 AFC U-23 Asian Cup]]. However, on 7 January 2026, he was called up to the roster after [[Ahmad Al-Moghrabi]] suffered a knee injury, as well as a need to have an additional attacking threat.<ref>{{cite web |title=ظهور باهت يعقد مهمة "الأولمبي".. والعزايزة يلتحق بصفوفه... |url=https://alghad.com/Section-180/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D8%B8%D9%87%D9%88%D8%B1-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%87%D8%AA-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%82%D8%AF-%D9%85%D9%87%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B2%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B2%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%AD%D9%82-%D8%A8%D8%B5%D9%81%D9%88%D9%81%D9%87-2061893 |website=alghad.com |publisher=Al-Ghad |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=7 January 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Hassan |first1=Fayez |title=منتخب الأردن يستنجد بمهاجم للقاء السعودية في كأس آسيا تحت 23 |url=https://www.winwin.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86-%D9%8A%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%86%D8%AC%D8%AF-%D8%A8%D9%85%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%AC%D9%85%C2%A0%D9%84%D9%84%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D9%83%D8%A3%D8%B3-%D8%A2%D8%B3%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%AA-23 |website=winwin.com |publisher=WinWin |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=7 January 2026}}</ref> Azaizeh would have an immediate impact for the team, as he would score two goals in Jordan's 3–2 win over [[Saudi Arabia national under-23 football team|Saudi Arabia]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jueles |first1=Mohannad |title=الأولمبي" في آسيا.. إصابة تربك الانطلاقة ونجم ينقذ المسار... |url=https://alghad.com/Section-180/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A2%D8%B3%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D8%A5%D8%B5%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%A8%D9%83-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%B7%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%82%D8%A9-%D9%88%D9%86%D8%AC%D9%85-%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%82%D8%B0-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%B1-2062238 |website=alghad.com |publisher=Al-Ghad |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=10 January 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=النشمي العزايزة يشكر الجماهير  مدار الساعة |url=https://alsaa.net/article/629071/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D8%B4%D9%85%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B2%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B2%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D8%B4%D9%83%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%87%D9%8A%D8%B1 |website=alsaa.net |publisher=Al-Saa'a |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=10 January 2026}}</ref> He then led Jordan to the quarter-finals, after scoring the winning goal against [[Kyrgyzstan national under-23 football team|Kyrgyzstan]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hassan |first1=Fayez |title=علي العزايزة يقود الأردن إلى ربع نهائي كأس آسيا تحت 23 عاما |url=https://www.winwin.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B2%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B2%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D8%AA%D9%83%D9%81%D9%84-%D8%A8%D8%AA%D8%A3%D9%87%D9%84-%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D9%83%D8%A3%D8%B3-%D8%A2%D8%B3%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%AA-23 |website=winwin.com |publisher=WinWin |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=12 January 2026}}</ref> Despite Jordan eventually getting eliminated on penalties against eventual champions [[Japan national under-23 football team|Japan]], Azaizeh managed to take the lead against Japan.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Trẻ |first1=Báo Tuổi |title=اليابان تحت 23 سنة ضد الأردن تحت 23 سنة (نهاية الشوط الأول) 0-1: علي العزايزة يفتتح التسجيل. |url=https://www.vietnam.vn/ar/u23-nhat-u23-jordan-het-hiep-1-0-1-ali-al-azaizeh-mo-ti-so |website=vietnam.vn |publisher=Vietnam.vn |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=16 January 2026}}</ref> Azaizeh was ultimately among the standout names of the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |title=#AFCU23 - Players who caught the eye |url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/national/afc_u23_asian_cup.html/news/afcu23-players-who-caught-the-eye |website=the-afc.com |publisher=Asian Football Confederation |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=English |date=26 January 2026}}</ref>

===Senior===
Azaizeh debuted for Jordan on 14 March 2025 during the 1–1 friendly draw against [[North Korea national football team|North Korea]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Jordan vs. North Korea 2025-03-14 |url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/matches/report/40988/Jordan_North_Korea.html |website=National Football Teams}}</ref>

He would get another Jordan call-up on 14 May 2025 for a preliminary roster,<ref>{{cite web |title=Road to 2026: Jordan's Extended Roster Revealed for High-Stakes Oman & Iraq Showdowns |url=https://petra.gov.jo/Include/InnerPage.jsp?ID=71470&lang=en&name=en_news |website=petra.gov.jo |publisher=Petra |access-date=3 July 2025 |language=English |date=14 May 2025}}</ref> subsequently getting another call up on 27 May 2025 for a [[Exhibition game#International football|friendly]] against [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia]] on 30 May and the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC third round]] matches against [[Oman national football team|Oman]] and [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] on 5 and 10 June 2025; respectively.<ref>{{cite news |title=إعلان قائمة النشامى لمعسكر الدمام ومواجهتي عُمان والعراق بتصفيات كأس العالم |url=https://www.jfa.jo/news.php?id=30468&title=%D8%A5%D8%B9%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%89-%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B9%D8%B3%D9%83%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85-%D9%88%D9%85%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%AA%D9%8A-%D8%B9%D9%8F%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82-%D8%A8%D8%AA%D8%B5%D9%81%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%83%D8%A3%D8%B3-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85 |access-date=27 May 2025 |publisher=الاتحاد الأردني لكرة القدم |date=23 May 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=National team faces Omani counterpart in World Cup qualifiers Thursday |url=https://en.ammonnews.net/article/82008 |website=ammonnews.net |publisher=Ammon News |access-date=3 July 2025 |language=English |date=6 June 2025}}</ref>

He also played during the 0–0 draw against [[Mali national football team|Mali]] on 18 November 2025.<ref name=":0" />

